# IPv4 address
## Class
Class A => range (0.0.0.0 to 127.255.255.255)   => N.H.H.H => 8 bits for network and 24 bits for hosts      ---> /8

Class B => range (128.0.0.0 to 191.255.255.255) => N.N.H.H => 16 bits for network and 16 bits for hosts     ---> /16

Class C => range (192.0.0.0 to 223.255.255.255) => N.N.N.H => 24 bits for network and 8 bits for hosts      ---> /24

Class D => range (224.0.0.0 to 239.255.255.255)

## Classless (CIDR vs VLSM)

## /30 